org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.common.task.flow

Class FlowScript

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.scripting.Script<FlowAction>
      • org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.common.task.flow.FlowScript
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @PublicAPI
public class FlowScript
extends Script<FlowAction>
    Dynamic evaluation of this script determines at runtime if a specific Control Flow operation should be performed in a TaskFlow.

    This class wraps information around a Script to determine which FlowAction is attached to this script.

    When using the action type FlowActionType.REPLICATE, the value of the replicateRunsVariable determines the number of parallel runs.

    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 2.2
    See Also:
    FlowAction, Serialized Form

      • setActionTarget

        public void setActionTarget(String target)
        If the Action type (see getActionType()) of this FlowScript is FlowActionType.LOOP, the target is the entry point of the next loop iteration. If the Action type is FlowActionType.IF, the target is the branch executed when the If condition succeeds.

        This value has no effect on the execution of the script

        Parameters:
        target - the main target of the action of this script.
